•   { N ≥ 0 } n,z:= 0,E { inv.(n,z) }

(1) E = ? // E = -∞

≡   Hoare triple

    N ≥ 0 ⇒ wp.(n,z:= 0,E).(inv.(n,z))

≡   Prove ⇒

    •   wp.(n,z:= 0,E).(inv.(n,z))

    (2) N ≥ 0

    ≡   Assignment

        inv.(0,E)

    ≡   Definition of inv

        ( n,z : 0 ≤ n ≤ N : z = m.n ).(0,E)

    ≡   λ comp

        •   0 ≤ 0 ≤ N // 0 ≤ N
        
        E = m.0

    ≡   Theory [0]

        E = -∞

    ■

⋯   true

■